### User-Trainer Relationship API Tests
### Base URL: http://localhost:8080

### 1. Create a new user-trainer relationship
POST http://localhost:8080/api/user-trainer-links?userId=admin&trainerId=trainer1
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 2. Get active trainers for a user
GET http://localhost:8080/api/user-trainer-links/user/admin/trainers
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 3. Get active users for a trainer
GET http://localhost:8080/api/user-trainer-links/trainer/trainer1/users
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 4. Check if user has access to trainer
GET http://localhost:8080/api/user-trainer-links/check-access?userId=admin&trainerId=trainer1
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 5. Get specific relationship
GET http://localhost:8080/api/user-trainer-links/relationship?userId=admin&trainerId=trainer1
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 6. Get all active relationships
GET http://localhost:8080/api/user-trainer-links/all-active
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 7. Assign multiple trainers to a user (bulk operation)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/user-trainer-links/bulk/user/demo/trainers
Content-Type: application/json

["trainer1", "trainer2"]

###

### 8. Assign multiple users to a trainer (bulk operation)
POST http://localhost:8080/api/user-trainer-links/bulk/trainer/trainer3/users
Content-Type: application/json

["admin", "demo"]

###

### 9. Deactivate a relationship (soft delete)
DELETE http://localhost:8080/api/user-trainer-links?userId=demo&trainerId=trainer2
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 10. Activate a relationship
PUT http://localhost:8080/api/user-trainer-links/activate?userId=demo&trainerId=trainer2
Content-Type: application/json

###

### 11. Update relationship status by ID (example with linkId=1)
PATCH http://localhost:8080/api/user-trainer-links/1?isActive=false
Content-Type: application/json

###

